The books lay piled atop each other with little in the way of rhyme or reason, yet atop the stack lays a thin red-leather bound journal.  Flipping to the back you read:

"I was never told there would be a seal on this door!  Blast!!  Despite all of my best efforts, I cannot seem to find the right spell to open the door.  I've been narrowing it down though, I think I've almost got it.  With a little more time and research perhaps.  What lies beyond is also mere speculation.  Perhaps I've been tricked, Blast!  I was a fool to trust that...wait...intruders come, I shall have  to continue this later..."

*The page ends abrubtly, the ink still fresh on the paper*
This chest seems to be brimming with all manner of ill-gotten goods.
